{
  "video_id": "b_n9qegR7C4",
  "title": "The psychology of post-traumatic stress disorder - Joelle Rabow Maletis",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 6903.0,
      "end_time": 10997.0,
      "text": "Many of us will experience some kind of trauma during our lifetime."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 10997.0,
      "end_time": 14227.0,
      "text": "Sometimes, we escape with no long-term effects."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 14227.0,
      "end_time": 18110.0,
      "text": "But for millions of us, those experiences linger,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18110.0,
      "end_time": 19801.0,
      "text": "causing symptoms like flashbacks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 19801.0,
      "end_time": 20708.0,
      "text": "nightmares,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 20708.0,
      "end_time": 23735.0,
      "text": "and negative thoughts  that interfere with everyday life."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 23735.0,
      "end_time": 27520.0,
      "text": "This phenomenon,  called post-traumatic stress disorder,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 27520.0,
      "end_time": 28450.0,
      "text": "or PTSD,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 28450.0,
      "end_time": 30439.0,
      "text": "isn’t a personal failing;"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 30440.0,
      "end_time": 34788.0,
      "text": "rather, it’s a treatable malfunction  of certain biological mechanisms"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 34788.0,
      "end_time": 39245.0,
      "text": "that allow us to cope  with dangerous experiences."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39245.0,
      "end_time": 40893.0,
      "text": "To understand PTSD,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 40893.0,
      "end_time": 45520.0,
      "text": "we first need to understand how the brain  processes a wide range of ordeals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 45520.0,
      "end_time": 47624.0,
      "text": "including the death of a loved one,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 47624.0,
      "end_time": 48884.0,
      "text": "domestic violence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 48884.0,
      "end_time": 50695.0,
      "text": "injury or illness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 50695.0,
      "end_time": 51744.0,
      "text": "abuse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 51744.0,
      "end_time": 52678.0,
      "text": "rape,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 52678.0,
      "end_time": 53468.0,
      "text": "war,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 53468.0,
      "end_time": 54412.0,
      "text": "car accidents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 54412.0,
      "end_time": 55946.0,
      "text": "and natural disasters."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 55947.0,
      "end_time": 59356.0,
      "text": "These events can bring on feelings  of danger and helplessness,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 59356.0,
      "end_time": 61583.0,
      "text": "which activate the brain’s alarm system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 61583.0,
      "end_time": 64968.0,
      "text": "known as  the “fight-flight-freeze” response."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 64968.0,
      "end_time": 66493.0,
      "text": "When this alarm sounds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 66493.0,
      "end_time": 69744.0,
      "text": "the hypothalamic, pituitary,  and adrenal systems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 69745.0,
      "end_time": 71677.0,
      "text": "known as the HPA axis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 71677.0,
      "end_time": 76640.0,
      "text": "work together to send signals  to the parasympathetic nervous system."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 76640.0,
      "end_time": 79827.0,
      "text": "That’s the network that communicates  with adrenal glands and internal organs"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 79828.0,
      "end_time": 82460.0,
      "text": "to help regulate functions like heart rate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 82460.0,
      "end_time": 82936.0,
      "text": "digestion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 82936.0,
      "end_time": 84589.0,
      "text": "and respiration."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 84589.0,
      "end_time": 86842.0,
      "text": "These signals start a chemical cascade"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 86842.0,
      "end_time": 90152.0,
      "text": "that floods the body with several  different stress hormones,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 90153.0,
      "end_time": 94580.0,
      "text": "causing physiological changes  that prepare the body to defend itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 94580.0,
      "end_time": 96155.0,
      "text": "Our heart rate speeds up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 96156.0,
      "end_time": 97163.0,
      "text": "breathing quickens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 97163.0,
      "end_time": 99470.0,
      "text": "and muscles tense."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 99470.0,
      "end_time": 101110.0,
      "text": "Even after a crisis is over,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 101110.0,
      "end_time": 104629.0,
      "text": "escalated levels of stress hormones  may last for days,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 104629.0,
      "end_time": 106215.0,
      "text": "contributing to jittery feelings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 106215.0,
      "end_time": 107370.0,
      "text": "nightmares,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 107370.0,
      "end_time": 108619.0,
      "text": "and other symptoms."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 108619.0,
      "end_time": 113182.0,
      "text": "For most people, these experiences disappear within a few days to two weeks"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 113182.0,
      "end_time": 115216.0,
      "text": "as their hormone levels stabilize."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 115216.0,
      "end_time": 118620.0,
      "text": "But a small percentage of those who experience trauma"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 118630.0,
      "end_time": 120208.0,
      "text": "have persistent problems"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 120208.0,
      "end_time": 124545.0,
      "text": "—sometimes vanishing temporarily  only to resurface months later."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 124545.0,
      "end_time": 127503.0,
      "text": "We don’t completely understand  what’s happening in the brain,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 127503.0,
      "end_time": 130564.0,
      "text": "but one theory is that  the stress hormone cortisol"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 130564.0,
      "end_time": 134589.0,
      "text": "may be continuously activating  the “fight-flight-freeze” response"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 134589.0,
      "end_time": 139864.0,
      "text": "while reducing overall brain functioning, leading to a number of negative symptoms."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 139864.0,
      "end_time": 142353.0,
      "text": "These symptoms often fall  into four categories:"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 142353.0,
      "end_time": 145441.0,
      "text": "intrusive thoughts,  like dreams and flashbacks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 145441.0,
      "end_time": 147418.0,
      "text": "avoiding reminders of the trauma,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 147418.0,
      "end_time": 151315.0,
      "text": "negative thoughts and feelings, like fear, anger, and guilt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 151315.0,
      "end_time": 156236.0,
      "text": "and “reactive” symptoms like irritability  and difficulty sleeping."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 156236.0,
      "end_time": 158719.0,
      "text": "Not everyone has all these symptoms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 158719.0,
      "end_time": 161672.0,
      "text": "or experiences them to the same extent  and intensity."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 161672.0,
      "end_time": 166531.0,
      "text": "When problems last more than a month,  PTSD is often diagnosed."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 166531.0,
      "end_time": 167485.0,
      "text": "Genetics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 167485.0,
      "end_time": 169736.0,
      "text": "on-going overwhelming stress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 169736.0,
      "end_time": 173464.0,
      "text": "and many risk factors  like preexisting mental illnesses"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 173464.0,
      "end_time": 174959.0,
      "text": "or lack of emotional support,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 174959.0,
      "end_time": 179272.0,
      "text": "likely play a role in determining  who will experience PTSD."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 179272.0,
      "end_time": 184613.0,
      "text": "But the underlying cause  is still a medical mystery."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 184613.0,
      "end_time": 189302.0,
      "text": "A major challenge of coping  with PTSD is sensitivity to triggers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 189302.0,
      "end_time": 191453.0,
      "text": "physical and emotional stimuli"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 191453.0,
      "end_time": 194375.0,
      "text": "that the brain associates  with the original trauma."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 194375.0,
      "end_time": 198354.0,
      "text": "These can be everyday sensations  that aren’t inherently dangerous"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 198354.0,
      "end_time": 201930.0,
      "text": "but prompt powerful physical  and emotional reactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 201930.0,
      "end_time": 204659.0,
      "text": "For example, the smell of a campfire"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 204659.0,
      "end_time": 208302.0,
      "text": "could evoke the memory of being trapped  in a burning house."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 208302.0,
      "end_time": 210209.0,
      "text": "For someone with PTSD,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 210209.0,
      "end_time": 213571.0,
      "text": "that memory activates the same neurochemical cascade"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 213571.0,
      "end_time": 215563.0,
      "text": "as the original event."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 215563.0,
      "end_time": 219583.0,
      "text": "That then stirs up the same feelings  of panic and helplessness"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 219584.0,
      "end_time": 223645.0,
      "text": "as if they’re experiencing  the trauma all over again."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 223645.0,
      "end_time": 227638.0,
      "text": "Trying to avoid these triggers, which are sometimes unpredictable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 227638.0,
      "end_time": 229741.0,
      "text": "can lead to isolation."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 229741.0,
      "end_time": 231775.0,
      "text": "That can leave people feeling invalidated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 231775.0,
      "end_time": 232529.0,
      "text": "ignored,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 232529.0,
      "end_time": 233894.0,
      "text": "or misunderstood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 233894.0,
      "end_time": 236385.0,
      "text": "like a pause button has been pushed on their lives"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 236385.0,
      "end_time": 239248.0,
      "text": "while the rest of the world  continues around them."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 239248.0,
      "end_time": 241620.0,
      "text": "But, there are options."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 241621.0,
      "end_time": 244123.0,
      "text": "If you think you might  be suffering from PTSD,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 244123.0,
      "end_time": 247827.0,
      "text": "the first step is an evaluation  with a mental health professional"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 247827.0,
      "end_time": 251155.0,
      "text": "who can direct you towards  the many resources available."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 251155.0,
      "end_time": 254385.0,
      "text": "Psychotherapy can  be very effective for PTSD,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 254385.0,
      "end_time": 257575.0,
      "text": "helping patients better  understand their triggers."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 257575.0,
      "end_time": 260402.0,
      "text": "And certain medications  can make symptoms more manageable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 260402.0,
      "end_time": 265181.0,
      "text": "as can self- care practices, like mindfulness and regular exercise."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 265182.0,
      "end_time": 269116.0,
      "text": "What if you notice signs of PTSD  in a friend or family member?"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 269116.0,
      "end_time": 273657.0,
      "text": "Social support, acceptance, and empathy are key to helping and recovery."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 273658.0,
      "end_time": 277187.0,
      "text": "Let them know you believe their account of what they’re experiencing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 277187.0,
      "end_time": 279730.0,
      "text": "and that you don’t blame them  for their reactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 279730.0,
      "end_time": 280970.0,
      "text": "If they’re open to it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 280970.0,
      "end_time": 283994.0,
      "text": "encourage them to seek evaluation  and treatment."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 283994.0,
      "end_time": 286880.0,
      "text": "PTSD has been called “the hidden wound”"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 286880.0,
      "end_time": 289608.0,
      "text": "because it comes  without outward physical signs."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 289608.0,
      "end_time": 294427.0,
      "text": "But even if it’s an invisible disorder,  it doesn’t have to be a silent one."
    }
  ]
}